Food Service and Text book Assistance Information:
In order to get textbook assistance, everyone must fill out the free and reduced application.
https://www.myschoolapps.com/Application
â€¢There is also a link at the bottom of the schoolâ€™s website titled: MySchoolApps
â€¢This application must be filled out every year, it does not transfer over from previous year
â€¢Success Academy location will be offering lunches and breakfasts to any student enrolled in either Career or Success.
â€¢School ID is required upon pickup, but a parent or guardian can bring student ID, students do not need to be present
â€¢All Success students are free, but Career students will be charged at their free/reduced/paid status.
â€¢The bulk meals will be offered on Tuesdays and Thursdays from 11AM to 12PM at the Success Academy location, beginning 8/11/2000.
â€¢If you have any questions relating to Foodservices, please email Steven Stutz at:
steven.stutz@compass-usa.com

post_text:
Parents of Career and Success Academy,
Check your email or text message, itâ€™s time to re-enroll your student for the 2020-21 school year!
Re-enrollment is our annual process to determine if your student will return for the next school year. This online process will take place on our SchoolMint site.
This is an important step to secure your students spot for the upcoming school year.
For each student, click Returning or Not Returning for the 2020-21 school year.
If your student is Returning, a Re-enroll button will appear for you to complete the required re-enrollment forms.
DO NOT click Add New Student. You are re-enrolling a current student.
DO NOT create a new account for your student(s)
If you have any questions about any required forms or need to speak to a school representative, please contact our office at enrollment@careeracademysb.com. If you encounter a technical error, please contact technical support at SchoolMint, support@schoolmint.com.

post_text:
SUMMER FOOD SERVICE at Success Academy!!!ðŸš¨ðŸš¨ðŸš¨ðŸš¨
Career and Success Academy has expanded its â€œSharing and Caringâ€ food service program to now include an off-site pick up location every Tuesday and Thursday from 11am-12pm.
Families can come to Apostolic House of Deliverance located at 4313 Linden Ave in South Bend. There will be three (3) breakfasts and three (3) lunch meals on Tuesdays, as well as four (4) breakfasts and four (4) lunch meals on Thursdays.
We will also continue to provide our food service at Success Academy! On Tuesdays, we offer three (3) breakfasts, three (3) lunch meals, and two (2) dinner meals to any children under 18.
Thursdays we offer four (4) breakfast, four (4) lunch meals, and three (3) dinner meals to any child under the age of 18.
Pick up for all pre-packaged meals is from 11am-12pm, every Tuesday and Thursday during the closure.
Enter and exit Success Academy at door B.

ðŸš¨ðŸš¨FOOD SERVICE UPDATEðŸš¨ðŸš¨
Career and Success Academy has expanded its â€œSharing and Caringâ€ food service program to now include an off-site pick up location every Tuesday and Thursday from 11am-12pm.
Families can come to Apostolic House of Deliverance located at 4313 Linden Ave in South Bend. There will be three (3) breakfasts and three (3) lunch meals on Tuesdays, as well as four (4) breakfasts and four (4) lunch meals on Thursdays.
We will also continue to provide our food service at Success Academy! On Tuesdays, we offer three (3) breakfasts, three (3) lunch meals, and two (2) dinner meals to any children under 18.
Thursdays we offer four (4) breakfast, four (4) lunch meals, and three (3) dinner meals to any child under the age of 18.
Pick up for all pre-packaged meals is from 11am-12pm, every Tuesday and Thursday during the closure.
Enter and exit Success Academy at door B.

Its that time of year again. Building our CASB Robotics Team for next year starts with you.
Mission Statement:
The Career Academy Wolf Pack Robotics Teamsâ€™ mission is to inspire young people to pursue fields in Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Mathematics (STEAM) by engaging them in exciting mentor-based programs. The program seeks to build 21st Century skills in related technical areas by fostering innovation and well-rounded life capabilities including self-confidence, problem-solving, teamwork, communication, and leadership.
Eligibility:
Each student is required to complete an application. Applications will need to be emailed to Mr. Ebersol as soon as possible. Please read the application carefully and answer all questions. The essay portion should reflect the qualifications you can bring to the team and/or what you want to learn by being on a robotics team.

https://youtu.be/ymOIA8mYydw

The Indiana Commission for Higher Education has extended the deadline to submit the 2020-2021 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA). Students who did not file the FAFSA before the April 15 deadline are encouraged to submit the form at FAFSA.gov as soon as possible. The Commission will consider students who file past the original deadline, however, limited funding is available on a first-come basis. The extension applies to the 21st Century Scholarship and the Frank Oâ€™Bannon Grant. There is no FAFSA deadline for Hoosiers applying for the Next Level Jobs Workforce Ready Grant.

post_text:
A message from the School Superintendent:

Parents/Guardians:
We are grateful for your continued patience and involvement as we navigate through these unprecedented times for our school, our community, and our country.
Our primary focus at this time is to maintain the health and wellness of our students, families, and staff, while supporting continued learning. Please be advised that both Career and Success Academy will be closed until May 1st, 2020 by order of the Governor of Indiana.
It is possible this date may be revised to extend through the end of the 2019-2020 school year if circumstances warrant. The Indiana Department of Education has canceled all state mandated assessments for this academic year. As we receive up-to-date information, we will continue to keep you informed.

Sincerely,
Alex Hammel
Superintendent of Schools

post_text: Go Trailblazers!!!
shared_text:
Career Academy Athletics
March 9 at 7:14 AM Â·

The CASB track runners competed for the second time at an Indoor Trine University track meet on Saturday (3/7/2020). McKenna D. led the girls in the 2-mile and ran a personal record with a time of 17:07 (8:03 1ST mile, followed by a 9:04 2nd mile). Nicola W. led the girls in the 60M dash with a time of 9.79, followed by Emily K-L with a time of 9.92, and Danielle W. with a time of 9.96. All 3 CASB runners ran a personal record in the 60M dash. The Distance Medley Relay Team ran a time of 18:29. Nicola W. ran a 5:05 1200M, Danielle W. ran a 1:33 400M, McKenna D. ran a 3:49 800M, and Emily K-L. ran a 8:01 mile in the relay.
Will R. led the boys in the 2-mile and ran a personal record with a time of 13:53 (6:46 1st mile, followed by a 7:07 2nd mile. Will R. also led the boys in the 60M dash with a time of 9.86, followed by Connor N. with a time of 9.89, and Krish N. with a time of 9.95. Will R. and Connor N. ran a personal in the 60M dash. Krish N. ran his second-best 60M dash of the indoor season.

The CASB track team had an Indoor meet at Trine University on Saturday (2/22/2020). The team had good chemistry, and this meet will be a building block going into the future. The girls had 4 runners compete. Danielle W. ran a 10.04 in the 60m dash, followed by a time of 36.26 in the 200m dash. Nicola W. ran a 7:10 mile, Emily K-L. ran a 7:44 mile, and McKenna D. ran a 7:47 mile. The boys had 3 runners compete. Will R. ran a mile-time of 6:26, tying his time of 6:26 from last year. Connor N. ran a 9.02 in the 60m dash, followed by a time of 31.29 in the 200m dash. Krish N ran a 9.41 in the 60m dash, followed by a time of 31.80 in the 200m dash.

The CASB track team had an Indoor meet at Trine University on Saturday (2/22/2020). The team had good chemistry, and this meet will be a building block going into the future. The girls had 4 runners compete. Danielle W. ran a 10.04 in the 60m dash, followed by a time of 36.26 in the 200m dash. Nicola W. ran a 7:10 mile, Emily K-L. ran a 7:44 mile, and McKenna D. ran a 7:47 mile. The boys had 3 runners compete. Will R. ran a mile-time of 6:26, tying his time of 6:26 from last year. Connor N. ran a 9.02 in the 60m dash, followed by a time of 31.29 in the 200m dash. Krish N ran a 9.41 in the 60m dash, followed by a time of 31.80 in the 200m dash.

post_text: The 7th Graders took a field trip over the last two days to the Mishawaka Water Treatment Facility. The two groups went on a tour of the facility that educated our students about the water cycle process, how the city pumps ground water, treats it, and then sends it out to local homes and businesses. There were lots of great questions posed by our students that really demonstrated how engaged they have been with this year's project based learning! It was very interesting to see how 2-3 million gallons of drinking water are treated every day! We are excited for the next few phases of our PBL and can't wait to show you all of our hard work!

Jobs for America's Graduates (JAG), Regional Career Development Conference was held on Friday, January 31, 2020, at the KROC Center South Bend, IN. This annual conference involved Fifteen (15) JAG programs from the following schools: Career Academy South Bend, John Adams, Riley, Penn Way, Washington, Rochester, Bremen, Tippecanoe, Warsaw, Goshen Merit, Elkhart Central, Elkhart Memorial, Goshen High School, Concord, and Wawasee. All known as Region 2.

Competitors competed in the following Categories:

Chapter Marketing Poster - Drawn & Created by Charity V. - CASB - 2nd Place
Chapter Marketing Commercial - Created by Karissa J. & Charity V. - CASB - 2nd Place
Overall Marketing - CASB - 3rd Place
Writing Skills - India D. - 3rd Place
Career Presentation - Micah R. - 3rd Place
Critical Thinking - Ian L. - 1st Place
Employability Skills - Karissa J. - 2nd Place
Financial Literacy - Rebecca S. - 2nd Place
